values:
I was starting the redesign of my blosxom blog (http://blog.tapdig.com) site. I was looking for inspiration for my dive into CSS adaptation and my multiple user idea. I hit some of my favorite bookmarks looking for examples of good design: "na, na, too plain, na, oh this is a really cool photographer's site, i remember this..." Then I proceed to hit view source to check it out, and what was the first thing I saw? <blockquote>...
&lt;meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=windows-1252"&gt;

&lt;meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 6.0"&gt;

&lt;meta name="ProgId" content="FrontPage.Editor.Document"&gt;
...</blockquote>
I ran. Shut the browser as fast as I could. nevermind. i'm still shivering and nauseous.

So anyway. I downloaded everything that runs blosxom, got it running locally fairly easily, i have not launched apache in a long while. actually only forgot the Win ActivePerl shebang#! but it's fine now. i've been running blosxom since October on Linux host only and this is the first time I've run it locally. this is also the first time i've thought about a redesign. My goal is to make it seem more like a photographer's site, and less like a blog. But still using a blog CMS for content. The learning curve is bitch. 1. Figure out theme/flavor system. 2. Fiddle with RSS feed. 3. CSS div BS. 4. Craptastic!

(warning: rant) I've been following recent discussion at the blosxom user group at yahoo about the CSS/XHTML plateau. Actually the discussion goes back to my beginnings in the group, and other groups and forums. I've always been "like screw validation" and "who has time to learn XHTML when I already know how to hand code HTML?" Besides, my CSS validates. Fuck standards. But now i've decided to scrap the tables, insert the divs. It's a leap for me, since I so violently resist the usability, accessibility, validation, bumper sticker to prove it, zeldman lover, oreilly preacher, web hackers... who are a lot like myself in several other ways. And I don't know anyone that visits my site from a cell phone. If you do, let me know. Or if you visit my site and you're blind, tell me. just curious. (/rant)

what do i resist more? standards or front page? btw, my frontpage horror originated from http://www.jenyk.com/ (home of really cool band photography, too much B+W images I thought)<img src="http://blog.tapdig.com/cgi-bin/tl/logs.pl" height=1 width=1>
